servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Modern
---

olive oil
1 packet button mushrooms
1 carrot
3 clove garlic
2 sprig rosemary
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
1 packet beef-style stock powder
30 g butter
1 packet filo pastry
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet beef mince
1 leek
1 avocado
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220ºC/200ºC fan-forced.
• Thinly slice leek and button mushrooms. Grate
the carrot. Finely chop garlic. Pick and finely
chop rosemary leaves.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over high heat. Cook mushrooms, leek and
carrot, stirring, until softened, 6-8 minutes.
• Add beef mince and cook, breaking it up with a
spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and rosemary and cook, stirring, until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add tomato paste,
the water and beef-style stock powder and
cook, stirring until reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season
to taste.

TIP: Add a dash more water if the mince is dry!

• Transfer beef filling to a baking dish, then
sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese.

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling
the cheese on top. Careful, the filling is hot!

• Add the butter to a small heatproof bowl and
microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Brush each sheet of the filo pastry with the
melted butter. Lightly scrunch each sheet
of pastry and place on top of beef filling to
completely cover.
• Bake pie until the pastry is golden,
15-20 minutes.

• While the pie is baking, roughly chop avocado.
• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves,
avocado and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and
olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide cheesy beef, mushroom and filo pastry
pie between plates.
• Serve with avocado and balsamic salad. Enjoy!